content: This app is an awesome resource. I like that it gives you examples of its use in sentences, depending on "he/she/them/you etc (I forget what that's called in linguistics) and also that it shows the word root. I love this app, amazing work, thankful to those who've worked to put this together, it's a great dictionary
It's awesome it's helped me understand and know how to say it the proper way to speak their language I really like this book I actually want to find a hard cover.
Wont download 🙁
Great app. Quick and easy to use.

I am so excited with this app! I love that is has pronunciation recordings. I just found out it cross-reference the Lakota words used in the definition examples too, making it very easy to learn to say whole phrases as well, with a "favorites" tab so I can practice the same words or phrases again and again. Amazing!!!
Excellent
Very easy to use and being able to hear the word pronounced is very helpful also.
Lila Waste
cant get out of dictionary without restarting my phone.
incredible!!! lila wast'é

The app stopped working, but I uninstalled it and installed it again and it works perfect! Best Lakota Language app I've come across.
Good dictionary. However, I wish it would do sentences with grammar explanations and tenses. Then it would be spectacular.

I've had the app for a while now and it just stopped working a month or so ago. It seems to be up to date... I love LLC and have their course materials, but wish I could get the app working again. If it works, it's the best out there. LLC is helping me learn the language of my husband's family and I hope to pass it to our soon to be born son.
I'm a tribal member that was born off the reservation and recently decided to try and learn the language. This app has been an amazing help!
I'll give it 5 stars cuz I love this app. I rated 1 before because it wouldn't download, but now that I was able to download it. I rerated it

content: I love this app; I have spent so many hours exploring it. The only downside is that the bookmarks page is neither intuitive nor user friendly. I accidentally wiped ALL my bookmarks early on trying to figure out how to navigate the page, and I'm unable to scroll past the first screen without changing the order of the bookmarks; you can drag and drop them and scroll that way, but if there's another way to scroll or view all your bookmarks, I don't know what it is. That one caveat aside, this is one of the best apps I've ever downloaded, and it's absolutely worth its price tag.
Phímàlèyé! Use it Often. Learn the Language & Teach other's. Make so pur `Lãkœkōtá Lak-otåyàyaí Could again buy & learn for less? Ìnjí?

I use this every day. Look up words quickly, hear their pronunciation, save your favorites, even see how a word is used in different ways (full text examples, especially useful with English words that don't translate exactly) Revolutionized my language study, again. Thanks LLC, Jan, Ben Black Bear, Iris, and everyone else behind this app's development! Does glitch every once in a while, reopening seems to solve it.
I love this app! My only wish is that I could build lists somewhere, like quizlet for word review. Otherwise couldn't ask for more :)

Very expansive. Everything I would hope for.

Although the full text search button needs to be used to lookup or access certain entries, and although I had to remove and reinstall it on my kids' tablets to get it to work properly, I find this a necessary tool in my and my kids' language learning. It is much easier to carry around than the paper version. I recently took this app hiking with my kids in Colorado -- to learn words for animals, insects, and plants encountered (it works without access to cell service, after the initial database download).
Does everything and more.. It's perfect

Love the pronunciation aspects and the sentence usage of words.  It's also nice that the Dakota spelling is included in the entry.  Good job, simple and classy layout makes it one of the best language dictionary I've ever downloaded.
Sound didn't work at first but I uninstalled, then I reinstalled and while the data downloaded I kept the screen from going dark. Now every entry is read aloud.
Download
replyContent: The dictionary does contain nearly 50 thousand audio files (for all the words), so it is larger than an average app, but not too large to prevent downloading. Let us know if you managed to download it in the end. Thank you
